<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>West Virginia Wins 21st NCAA National Championship, Sets NCAA Championship Record</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/rifle-west-virginia-wins-21st-ncaa-national-championship-sets-ncaa-championship-record</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/rifle-west-virginia-wins-21st-ncaa-national-championship-sets-ncaa-championship-record</guid><category>Rifle</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="2026 Rifle NCAA National Champions" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" /><br /><br />COLUMBUS, Ohio – For the 21st time in program history, the West Virginia University rifle team won the NCAA Rifle National Championship after two days of competition inside the Covelli Center in Columbus on Saturday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg"><media:title>2026 Rifle NCAA National Champions</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 15:39:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>8</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58864</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia to Host NCAA Tournament First and Second Rounds</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/womens-basketball-west-virginia-to-host-ncaa-tournament-first-and-second-rounds</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/womens-basketball-west-virginia-to-host-ncaa-tournament-first-and-second-rounds</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="we're hosting 1920x1080" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University women's basketball team is set to host the First and Second Rounds of the 2026 NCAA Women's Basketball Tournament, as announced by the NCAA on Saturday afternoon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png"><media:title>we're hosting 1920x1080</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 15:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58863</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Tally Six Season Highs in Regular-Season Finale</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/gymnastics-mountaineers-tally-six-season-highs-in-regular-season-finale</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/gymnastics-mountaineers-tally-six-season-highs-in-regular-season-finale</guid><category>Gymnastics</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="carlee nelson" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/15/031326_GYMN_TL-33.jpg" /><br /><br />PITTSBURGH, Pa. – Behind six individual season-high scores, the West Virginia University gymnastics team scored a 195.35 to finish in second place in a tri meet at Pitt with Illinois State inside Fitzgerald Field House in Pittsburgh on Sunday afternoon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/031326_GYMN_TL-33.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/031326_GYMN_TL-33.jpg"><media:title>carlee nelson</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/031326_GYMN_TL-33.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 17:57:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>11</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58870</s:story_id></item><item><title>Wilson’s Final Round 64 Leads WVU to a Third-Place Finish</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/golf-wilsons-final-round-64-leads-wvu-to-a-third-place-finish</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/golf-wilsons-final-round-64-leads-wvu-to-a-third-place-finish</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Nemacolin Collegiate Invitational action" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2025/9/30/4_GOLF_ACTION_pxwnd.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For the second round in a row, a West Virginia University golfer shot an 8-under-par 64 at the Schenkel Invitational. This time, it was senior Kaleb Wilson who did so to finish third and to lead the Mountaineers to their best-ever finish at the Schenkel Invitational on Sunday in Statesboro, Georgia.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/30/4_GOLF_ACTION_pxwnd.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/30/4_GOLF_ACTION_pxwnd.jpg"><media:title>Nemacolin Collegiate Invitational action</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/30/4_GOLF_ACTION_pxwnd.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 16:45:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58869</s:story_id></item><item><title>Yehl, Mountaineers Shut Out Baylor to Take Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/baseball-yehl-mountaineers-shut-out-baylor-to-take-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/baseball-yehl-mountaineers-shut-out-baylor-to-take-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/15/ENX09847.jpeg" /><br /><br />WACO, Texas – A dominant performance on the mound from redshirt junior Maxx Yehl paved the way for an 8-0 victory for the West Virginia University baseball team over Baylor, Sunday afternoon at Baylor Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 13-4 overall and 2-1 in the Big 12 while the Bears fall to 11-8 and 1-2 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/ENX09847.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/ENX09847.jpeg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/ENX09847.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 16:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58868</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Bounce Back to Even Series Against Baylor</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/baseball-mountaineers-bounce-back-to-even-series-against-baylor</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/baseball-mountaineers-bounce-back-to-even-series-against-baylor</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tyrus Hall" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/ENX09262.jpeg" /><br /><br />WACO, Texas – The West Virginia University baseball team evened up the series with Baylor, Saturday afternoon, defeating the Bears, 13-2, in seven innings. The Mountaineers improve to 12-4 overall and 1-1 in conference play while Baylor falls to 11-7 and 1-1 in the Big 12.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/ENX09262.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/ENX09262.jpeg"><media:title>Tyrus Hall</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/ENX09262.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 19:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58867</s:story_id></item><item><title>Michael’s 8-Under-Par 64 Leads WVU on Saturday</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/golf-michaels-8-under-par-64-leads-wvu-on-saturday</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/golf-michaels-8-under-par-64-leads-wvu-on-saturday</guid><category>Golf</ca