 url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/GB707914.jpg"><media:title>Julie Bousseau</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/GB707914.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 17:16:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>15</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58865</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Drop Big 12 Opener to Baylor</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/baseball-mountaineers-drop-big-12-opener-to-baylor</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/baseball-mountaineers-drop-big-12-opener-to-baylor</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Brock Wills" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg" /><br /><br />WACO, Texas – The West Virginia University baseball team dropped its Big 12 opener, 7-6, Friday evening at Baylor. The Mountaineers fall to 11-4 overall while the Bears improve to 11-6.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg"><media:title>Brock Wills</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 23:22:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58862</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Scores Fourth Straight 195.0+ Score at No. 21 NC State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/gymnastics-west-virginia-scores-